    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Since I read that Lodash's `isFinite` relies on `Number.isFinite`, I thought that would be fine. Good catch.\r\n\r\nWe can use the top-level [`isFinite`](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/isFinite) function which is supported on IE.",
